# Playwright testing (agents)

## Default: Playwright CLI (`@playwright/test`)

Use the **CLI** for regression, bug fixes, and ‚Äúdid we break anything?‚Äù after code changes.

- Specs live in `e2e/*.spec.ts`; config in `playwright.config.ts`
- **Notes**: `npm run test:e2e:notes` (local mock + starts dev on :3001)
- **Notes mobile**: `npm run test:e2e:notes-mobile` (390√ó844 touch viewport, `e2e/notes-mobile.spec.ts`)
- **Notes prod**: `PLAYWRIGHT_SKIP_WEBSERVER=1 npm run test:e2e:notes` or `npm run test:e2e:notes-deploy`
- Prefer **mock routes** (`e2e/helpers/*-mock.ts`) for AI/sync ‚Äî deploy specs only when testing real APIs
- Do **not** use `PLAYWRIGHT_SKIP_WEBSERVER=1` against `127.0.0.1:3001` unless `npm run dev -- -p 3001` is already running
- After substantive Notes edits: `verify:notes-*` ‚Üí `test:e2e:notes` until green; add/extend specs for new behavior

## When to use Cursor Playwright plugin (MCP `plugin-playwright-playwright`)

Use the **plugin** only when CLI is insufficient ‚Äî same Playwright APIs, **not** a replacement for the test suite.

**Enable (repo):** [`.cursor/settings.json`](../settings.json) ‚Üí `"claude-plugins-official/playwright": { "enabled": true }` (one plugin; MCP id **`plugin-playwright-playwright`**). Do **not** also add a short `"playwright"` entry or manual `mcp.json` ‚Äî that duplicates the same MCP. If tools missing: Cursor **Settings ‚Üí Plugins** ‚Üí install **Playwright** (Microsoft) ‚Üí **Tools & MCP** ‚Üí enable ‚Üí **Reload Window**.

**Invoke:** agent calls MCP tools via `CallMcpTool` with `server: "plugin-playwright-playwright"` (e.g. `browser_navigate`, `browser_snapshot`, `browser_take_screenshot`, `browser_console_messages`).

**Use plugin for:**
- ‚ÄúTry this flow and tell me what you see‚Äù (human QA you‚Äôd do manually)
- Visual/layout sanity on **https://sfjc.dev** (toolbar, panel, mobile viewport)
- Reproducing a **subjective** bug (cursor jump, wrong spacing, console errors)
- Quick smoke before/after a fix when writing a full spec isn‚Äôt worth it yet

**Plugin tools:** `browser_navigate`, `browser_snapshot`, `browser_run_code_unsafe` (ad-hoc `page` scripts)

**Do not use plugin for:**
- CI-style regression (no parallel suite, no `page.route` mocks, no HTML report/traces)
- Proving a fix ‚Äî always confirm with CLI after

## Workflow

1. **Implement fix** ‚Üí run relevant **CLI** tests
2. If user reports ‚Äúfeels wrong on the site‚Äù ‚Üí **plugin** smoke on prod ‚Üí capture snapshot/console ‚Üí then **CLI** test if reproducible
3. Promote repeated plugin checks into **`e2e/*.spec.ts`**

## Cross-browser (Playwright CLI only)

Use Playwright **projects** in `playwright.config.ts` (`chromium`, `Mobile Chrome`, `visual-*`). For prod smoke: `npm run test:e2e:notes-deploy` (targets **https://sfjc.dev**). For local full suite: `npm run test:e2e:notes`.
